25. ****** Landscape technical guide on min maxing performance and quality of graphics
https://docs.unrealengine.com/4.27/en-US/BuildingWorlds/Landscape/TechnicalGuide/

26. Height maps are black and white texture data that unreal engine reads to figure out troughs, valleys, and peaks in your landscape terrain. Black is for lows, white
is for high peaks. 1px / 1 pixel = 1 meter. A resoultion of 1000px by 1000px means you have a 1000 by 1000 meter landscape size
https://www.worldofleveldesign.com/categories/ue4/landscape-heightmap-guide.php

27. **** Creating custom height maps to create real world landscapes using terrain.party
https://www.udemy.com/course/unreal-engine-4-level-design-with-landscapes/learn/lecture/15663542#overview

28. Pressing the "END" key snaps objects to the floor. Been looking for this for millions of years.

29. You can select "hotkey" actor objects by pressing ctrl+1 etc like in RTS keys to bookmark important units/objects. Press 1 or whatever corresponding key to warp
instantly to that important bookmarked object.

